The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the National Archives in Washington, D.C. to celebrate the Fourth of July with 44 new American citizens. He commended the new citizens for going through the legal immigration process and becoming part of the freest and most prosperous nation in the world. Pence acknowledged the challenges faced by the current immigration system but emphasized the generosity of America's legal immigration system. He also reminded the new citizens of the importance of vigilance and sacrifice in maintaining freedom. Pence shared a personal story about his Irish immigrant grandfather and encouraged the new citizens to use their newfound citizenship for the benefit of their families, communities, and the nation. He concluded by urging them to dream big and pursue their American dreams.